Heat broiler to high. Place 4 @wooden skewers{8}(for 2 servings) in a shallow
#dish{} and cover with water to soak.

Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}; grate remaining half on the
largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a small #pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @onion{1/2}(peeled and diced) and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring
often, until lightly browned and softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), half the
@chicken stock concentrate{1}, and 1/2 tsp @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}.
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to a low simmer. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, bring @butter{1%tablespoon} to room temperature. Wash and dry
produce.

Finely dice @tomato{1}. Trim and finely dice @mini cucumber{1}. Quarter
@lemon{1}.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce}, @onion{1/2}(grated),
remaining shawarma spice blend, remaining stock concentrate, 3/4 tsp
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Divide beef mixture into four equal portions (eight
portions for 4). Roll each portion into a thin log on a #cutting board{}. Press
each log around a skewer, sealing the meat and leaving 2-3 inches of skewer
uncovered at the bottom.

Place beef skewers on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Broil until cooked
through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

While beef skewers roast, in a second medium bowl, combine tomato,
cucumber, juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), a drizzle of
@olive oil{4%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

In a third medium bowl, whisk together @hummus{4%tablespoon},
@olive oil{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of salt and pepper, and a squeeze of lemon
juice to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency.

Toast @whole wheat pitas{2}. Spread pitas with softened butter, then cut each
into four pieces.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice, beef skewers, tomato salad, and pitas between bowls. Drizzle
skewers with lemony hummus. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160º.